The Gunma Bank Ltd is issuing a 50 mlndlr convertible eurobond due March 31, 2002 paying an indicated2-1/4 pct and priced at par, lead manager Nomura InternationalLtd said.    The issue is callable from March 31, 1990 at 104 pctdeclining by 1/2 pct per annum to par thereafter but is notcallable until 1992 unless the share price exceeds 150 pct ofthe conversion price.    The selling concession is 1-1/2 pct while management andunderwriting combined pays one pct. Final terms will be fixedon March 12.    The issue is available in denominations of 5,000 dlrs andwill be listed in Luxembourg. The payment date is March 31.    The conversion period is from April 13, 1987 until March22, 2002. REUTER&#3;